==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Saxon [[gewin]], Old High German [[giwin]] (German [[Gewinn]] ‘gain’).  Compare [[gewinnan]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/jeˈwɪn:/}}

===Noun===
'''ġewinn''' {{n}} (plural same)
